Key Match Events: England won by 8 wickets (with 101 balls remaining)
Adil Rashid took 4 wickets for 11 runs
Jofra Archer took 3 wickets for 12 runs
Mark Wood took 3 wickets for 12 runs
Post-Match Reflections: England are back in the game

Assuming England can achieve a further two points against Namibia on Saturday, Scotland will be left with the daunting task of beating the Group B leaders Australia if they hope to progress to the Super Eight
Miscellaneous Highlights: England needed not only to win, but to win quickly, given Scotland's near four-point edge in the net run-rate stakes
Others: Reece Topley returned to the England squad after recovering from an injury
